==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water glass
<hw>Wa"ter glass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>See <cref>Soluble glass</cref>, under <er>Glass</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A clepsydra.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An instrument consisting of an open box or tube with
a glass bottom, used for examining objects in the water, as upon the sea
bottom in shallow places.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A water gauge for a steam boiler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water god</ent>⟦br⟧
